      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_CalculationStageResultDelete",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to delete records from the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "StagingBudget",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table within the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "budget",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema. It specifically targets records that match a given "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ScenarioId",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "BudgetStageID",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". This procedure is typically used in scenarios where data needs to be removed from a staging area, possibly as part of a data refresh or cleanup process."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity of this stored procedure is low. It performs a straightforward DELETE operation based on two input parameters. There are no conditional logic, loops, or complex operations involved."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
